Scam Trends

Current Top Scams

Safe Account Scam: Fraudsters pose as bank staff, urging you to move money to a “safe” account.

Crypto Giveaway: Fake promises of doubled investments if you send cryptocurrency first.

Parcel Scams: Texts or emails claiming a delivery fee is due, leading to phishing links.

New Tactics Emerging

AI Voice Scams: Scammers use voice cloning to impersonate loved ones or officials, requesting urgent funds.

New

Scams Pretending to Be Banks or HMRC

Fraudsters mimic official emails or calls from banks or HMRC, often citing tax refunds or account issues to extract personal details or payments.

Trending

Examples of Recent Scam Messages

“Your package is held at the depot. Pay £2.99 to release it: [link]”

“HMRC: You’re due a refund of £342. Click to claim: [link]”

Note: Links sanitized for safety.

); } export default ScamTrends;
